{"actor":"Erik Schneider","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-11T14:03:32Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":"ca260b98-b48c-4a12-8f78-cf4bd08b61d4","issue_id":"referee-j52","new_value":"{\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"referee-j52\",\"title\":\"Fix exposed RDP server on referee-project.com\",\"description\":\"Cloudflare detected TCP connections succeeding on port 3389 (RDP) for referee-project.com. This exposes internal resources to the public internet. Need to investigate DNS records and either remove the offending record, proxy it through Cloudflare, or set up Access policies.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":0,\"issue_type\":\"bug\",\"owner\":\"erik@phinonce.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-11T13:03:20Z\",\"created_by\":\"Erik Schneider\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-11T13:03:20Z\"}"}
{"actor":"Erik Schneider","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-11T14:07:16Z","event_type":"updated","id":"f6dae0ed-8e45-4ef3-99df-6bfd8870ca32","issue_id":"referee-j52","new_value":"{\"notes\":\"## Root Cause\\nPort 3389 is open on Vercel's infrastructure IPs (216.198.79.1 and 76.76.21.21). This is not specific to our deployment - it's a Vercel infra characteristic. The root domain A record is DNS-only (grey cloud), exposing the origin IP directly.\\n\\n## Fix Required\\nEnable Cloudflare proxy (orange cloud) on the root A record for referee-project.com:\\n\\n1. Go to Cloudflare Dashboard \\u003e referee-project.com \\u003e DNS \\u003e Records\\n2. Find the A record for 'referee-project.com' pointing to 216.198.79.1\\n3. Click Edit and toggle the proxy status from 'DNS only' (grey cloud) to 'Proxied' (orange cloud)\\n4. Save\\n\\nThis will:\\n- Hide the origin Vercel IP behind Cloudflare\\n- Block all non-HTTP/S ports (including 3389/RDP)\\n- Resolve the security insight\\n\\n## Why API fix failed\\nThe CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN only has zone:read + worker:read/edit permissions. Needs 'DNS:Edit' permission added to modify records programmatically.\\n\\n## Alternative\\nUpdate the API token at https://dash.cloudflare.com/4405ec6efc151efbbd966c70724d19a0/api-tokens to include 'Zone DNS Edit' permission, then we can automate this.\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"referee-j52\",\"title\":\"Fix exposed RDP server on referee-project.com\",\"description\":\"Cloudflare detected TCP connections succeeding on port 3389 (RDP) for referee-project.com. This exposes internal resources to the public internet. Need to investigate DNS records and either remove the offending record, proxy it through Cloudflare, or set up Access policies.\",\"status\":\"in_progress\",\"priority\":0,\"issue_type\":\"bug\",\"owner\":\"erik@phinonce.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-11T13:03:20Z\",\"created_by\":\"Erik Schneider\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-11T13:03:32Z\"}"}
